## Summary

Tested 31 properties across 4 django.core modules - all passed ✅

### Modules Tested:

1. **django.core.signing** (7 properties)
   - dumps/loads round-trip with various data types
   - b64_encode/decode round-trip
   - b62_encode/decode round-trip
   - Signing with compression
   - Unicode and nested structure handling

2. **django.core.paginator** (6 properties)
   - Item count preservation across pages
   - Page size invariants
   - Correct num_pages calculation
   - Orphan behavior
   - Edge cases with empty/single-item lists

3. **django.core.validators** (9 properties)
   - Min/Max value validator consistency
   - Length validators
   - Decimal validator precision
   - Email/URL validation robustness
   - IPv4 address validation
   - Null character prohibition
   - Regex validator with inverse matching

4. **django.core.cache** (9 properties)
   - set/get round-trip
   - add() semantics (only sets if key doesn't exist)
   - get_or_set behavior
   - delete() return values
   - None value handling
   - Timeout expiration
   - Cache versioning isolation
   - Special character key support

All 31 property-based tests passed successfully with thousands of randomized inputs generated by Hypothesis. No bugs were found in django.core - the module appears robust and handles edge cases well.
